refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;

 public
 stringZookeeper::get
 stringpath
 callablewatcher_cb&null;
 arraystat&null;
 intmax_size0

&reftitle.errors;


 This method emits PHP error/warning when parameters count or types are wrong or fail to get value from node.




    Since version 0.3.0, this method emits ZookeeperException and it's derivatives.

  &reftitle.examples;

   Zookeeper::get example


     Get value from node.



<?php
$zookeeper = new Zookeeper('locahost:2181');
$path = '/path/to/node';
$value = 'nodevalue';
$zookeeper->set($path, $value);

$r = $zookeeper->get($path);
if ($r)
  echo $r;
else
  echo 'ERR';
?>


   &example.outputs;


nodevalue





   Zookeeper::get stat example


     Get node stat info.



<?php
$zookeeper = new Zookeeper('localhost:2181');
$path = '/path/to/node';
$stat = [];
$zookeeper->get($path, null, $stat);
var_dump($stat);
?>


